description:
The ACLU is our nation's guardian of liberty, working daily in courts, legislatures and communities to defend and preserve the individual rights and liberties that the Constitution and laws of the United States guarantee everyone in this country. The ACLU is a nonprofit and nonpartisan organization that has grown from a roomful of civil liberties activists in 1920 to an organization of more than 500,000 members and supporters today. We handle nearly 6,000 court cases annually from our offices in almost every state.

The ACLU is supported by annual dues and contributions from its members, plus grants from private foundations and individuals. We do not receive any government funding. 

We protect:
Your First Amendment rights - freedom of speech, association and assembly; freedom of the press, and freedom of religion. 
Your right to equal protection under the law - protection against unlawful discrimination. 
Your right to due process - fair treatment by the government whenever the loss of your liberty or property is at stake. 
Your right to privacy - freedom from unwarranted government intrusion into your personal and private affairs. 
The ACLU also works to extend rights to segments of our population that have traditionally been denied their rights, including people of color; women; lesbians, gay men, bisexuals and transgender people; prisoners; and people with disabilities.
generated_description:
## ACLU: A Snapshot

The American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) is a stalwart defender of rights and liberties in the United States. Founded in 1920, it began as a small group of civil liberties activists and has grown into a powerhouse, boasting over 500,000 members and supporters nationwide. With a dedicated team of about 1,700 employees, the ACLU operates from almost every state, tackling approximately 6,000 court cases annually.

### Mission and Purpose

The ACLU’s mission is straightforward yet profound: to preserve the individual rights and liberties guaranteed to all people by the U.S. Constitution and laws. This nonprofit, nonpartisan organization strives to protect a broad array of rights, including:

- **First Amendment Rights:** Protecting freedoms related to speech, assembly, press, and religion.
- **Equal Protection:** Fighting against unlawful discrimination.
- **Due Process:** Ensuring fair treatment in legal proceedings.
- **Privacy Rights:** Defending individuals from unwarranted government intrusions.

Moreover, the ACLU is dedicated to fighting for marginalized groups who have historically faced rights denials, including people of color, women, and LGBTQ+ individuals.

### Funding and Affiliation

Uniquely positioned among organizations of its ilk, the ACLU does not accept government funding. It relies entirely on membership dues, private contributions, and grants from foundations and individuals, which empowers it to advocate independently and vigorously.

### Notable Issues and Initiatives

The ACLU actively engages in various social justice issues such as:

- **Reproductive Freedom:** Advocating for the right to make personal health decisions.
- **Racial Justice:** Addressing systemic inequalities and discriminatory practices.
- **Voting Rights:** Protecting access to the ballot box for all citizens.
- **Transgender Rights:** Championing the rights and dignity of transgender individuals.

In the face of ongoing threats to civil liberties, the ACLU's action is more critical than ever. They engage with communities, lobby for legislative changes, and fight in court whenever rights are violated.

### Historical Impact

The ACLU has a storied history as a pioneer in civil rights advocacy. Over the decades, its legal battles have significantly influenced American law and society. Key milestones include:

- **Defending Japanese Americans** during their internment in WWII.
- Winning the landmark **Loving v. Virginia** case which overturned bans on interracial marriage.
- Advocating for **same-sex marriage rights** in the landmark case of Obergefell v. Hodges.

### Get Involved

Anyone looking to support civil liberties can join the ACLU through donations or volunteer opportunities. They encourage grassroots activism through their People Power platform, allowing individuals to partake in various advocacy efforts.

For more detailed information about their ongoing work and campaigns, you can visit the ACLU’s website at [aclu.org](https://www.aclu.org/).

In essence, the ACLU embodies a commitment to uphold and extend the liberties and rights that are foundational to American democracy—an endeavor as vital today as it was over a century ago.
headline: Defender of rights and liberties
name: ACLU

description:
We’re on a mission to optimize the agricultural industry.

When we started Bountiful in 2015, the grape error rate for predicting production was 30 percent. Why? We found that many farmers in the specialty crops space were still using traditional pencil-and-paper techniques to predict yield. These low-fidelity forecasting methods weren’t giving them a clear enough understanding of their production until it was too late, leading to waste and inefficiency throughout the supply chain.

We saw a problem we wanted to solve.

Today, Bountiful is using advanced data science to help farmers forecast more accurately, so they can make better decisions. In the last three years, we’ve combined the latest in machine learning with weather, satellite, geographic, and historical data. The result is a user-friendly platform that transforms volumes of complex agricultural information into simple, actionable insights farmers can use to run more economically and environmentally sustainable farms.

More recently, we’re working to open the dialogue between buyers and sellers, remove uncertainty, and provide clarity to the supply chain to meet global food demand.

Our ultimate goal is to close the agricultural margin of error. Not only will this make individual farms more efficient, profitable, and sustainable, but it will help optimize the global food supply chain. That means healthier people and a healthier planet.

description:
At Extern, we’re solving the experience gap.  Extern created the remote Externship, a skill-building work experience that is easier for students to access, and easier for companies to run, than an internship.  Our mission is to help anyone discover and launch their career through professional experiences available anywhere at any time.  Since 2020, we’ve created and powered Externships on behalf of companies from Fortune 500s to startups that have enabled tens of thousands of students to build real experience and open doors to incredible opportunity.  

After spending $100K on average for a 4-year degree, graduates find that almost 40% of entry level jobs on Linkedin required 3+ years of work experience. Internships are how many college students get this kind of experience, but the demand for good internships outstrips the supply. Internship programs are difficult to scale, they favor students who already have social capital, and they’re time-consuming for employers to run.

Externships are short, online, project-based work experiences that employers can offer to hundreds of students using less resource and employee time than it would take to support an intern.  Extern makes the complex process of running an Externship completely turnkey with software and industry experts which in turn makes professional experience more accessible to more students.

By making work experience more accessible, Extern is driving the rapid mobility and upskilling needed for a new economy.  We envision a world where anyone can access work experience as a form of education – no matter their background, experience, or socio-economic status.  Come join our movement to reshape work, education, and credentialing for future generations with the Externship.

Extern was born out of a pivot from Paragon One (W17) which initially focused on providing students with a career center-as-a-service platform, connecting them with industry professionals to receive career coaching and guidance.  Backed by Y Combinator, Foundation Capital, Launch Fund, University Ventures, and Learn Capital.

generated_description:
**Indee Labs: Innovating T Cell Immunotherapy**

Founded in 2015 and based in Berkeley, CA, Indee Labs is a biotech company on a mission to revolutionize T cell immunotherapy. As part of the Y Combinator Batch W17, they have charged ahead to tackle one of the largest hurdles in the field: intracellular delivery. Most traditional methods struggle with efficiency and cell viability, and that's where Indee Labs' patented technology comes into play.

### **The Technology**

Indee Labs specializes in a non-viral delivery system known as Hydropore™, which utilizes **microfluidic vortex shedding** (_µVS_). This innovative approach allows for the rapid delivery of nucleic acids, proteins, and gene-editing complexes directly to patient and donor T cells—doing so with minimal disruption. Picture it like an express lane for cellular therapies, where you can yield millions to billions of healthy, functional cells in mere seconds.

This technology significantly circumvents the limitations seen with viral transduction and traditional electroporation methods, providing a more efficient path from research and development through to large-scale manufacturing.

### **Current Activities**

The compact team of five at Indee Labs is currently focused on several exciting initiatives, including partnerships and ongoing development for their Hydropore™ system. They’ve recently secured strategic investments, collaborated with companies like GenScript and Monomer Bio to enhance their offerings, and adopted cutting-edge tools like Scispot to streamline their operations.

Notable recent announcements include an exclusive distribution deal with Sunko Instruments in China for Hydropore™, showcasing their commitment to expanding their global reach. 

### **Key Takeaways**

- **Founded**: 2015  
- **Location**: Berkeley, CA  
- **Team Size**: 5 employees  
- **Specialization**: Non-viral delivery systems for T cell immunotherapy  
- **Technological Edge**: Hydropore™ utilizing microfluidic vortex shedding  
- **Partnerships**: Collaborations with major biotech entities to enhance research and development capabilities  

Indee Labs represents an exciting beacon of innovation in gene and cell therapy, driving forward with the promise of better, more effective treatments for various diseases through engineered T cell therapies. description:
We enable humans & machines with internet connectivity at a price that they can afford.

The inspiration for Wifi Dabba came from the founders working together for the last decade in the mobile application industry and realising the biggest reason for user churn being access to cheap and affordable internet access. From having worked on ground onboarding users and facing poor connectivity issues all the time, we took it on ourselves to fix the internet access problem for the common citizen.

At Wifi Dabba (YC W17), we are building a low cost, scalable & distributed Wi-Fi infrastructure to connect next billion users online. We do this by deploying a grid of lasers (Free Space Optics) over the cities & town and bring cheap and fast internet for everyone. We enable anyone to buy 1 gig of data access at a time at a price they can afford. Sachetization of internet access is the foundation to rebuilding internet for all. We do this by leveraging crypto and blockchain to truly make internet infrastructure ownership distributed — our vision is to be connectivity layer for the Web3 world.

generated_description:
**Wifi Dabba, Inc.** is pioneering a new era in connectivity with its mission of decentralized broadband for everyone. Founded in 2017 and part of Y Combinator’s Winter 2017 batch, this Bengaluru-based startup aims to address a common pain point: the lack of affordable internet access—especially vital for India's millions of potential users.

The team behind Wifi Dabba has over a decade of experience in mobile applications, where they saw firsthand how poor internet connectivity led to user churn. Realizing that the solution lies beyond conventional methods, they innovated a model that employs a distributed mesh of Wi-Fi infrastructure built on Free Space Optics (laser technology). This approach allows Wifi Dabba to offer internet access at very low costs, enabling anyone to buy data in flexible increments.

By harnessing crypto and blockchain technology, Wifi Dabba is reshaping internet ownership and access—creating a Web3 connectivity layer that emphasizes equity. Their offerings include Dabba Lite and Dabba Pro hotspots, which can be managed by local cable operators (LCOs), further empowering community-level deployment and maintenance.

As of now, Wifi Dabba's network boasts over 2,200 hotspots and has consumed 1,600 TB of data, illustrating the demand for their services. With a small yet dedicated team of 21 employees and support from notable investors like Multicoin Capital and Borderless Capital, they are working to connect the next billion users.

The Dabba Token (DBT) operates as the backbone of its ecosystem, incentivizing participants and aiding in managing supply through a burn mechanism connected to data consumption.

To explore more about their offerings or track their progress, you can visit their website at [Wifi Dabba](https://dabba.com), or join their discussions on [Discord](https://dabba.com/<https:/dab.ba/discord>). This is a classic example of leveraging innovative tech to solve real-world problems and democratize access to information.
headline: Decentralised broadband connectivity.
